title: Great Barrier Reef in American Sameo shore
moreinfo: Based on the worldês most extensive time series data on reef condition (2,258 surveys of 214 reefs over 1985_2012), the article cited has shown a major decline in coral cover from 28.0% to 13.8% (0.53% y_1), a loss of 50.7% of initial coral cover. The XL Catlin Seaview Survey is a unique global study dedicated to monitoring the change in coral reef and communicating it to the world.
